WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:06:07.377 --> 00:06:08.879
Do you come here often?

3
00:06:08.962 --> 00:06:10.255
Alone?

4
00:06:22.434 --> 00:06:25.854
What will you have. Mother?
Scotch. vodka?

5
00:06:25.938 --> 00:06:30.400
No. it's too early for that.
I'll have a Cinzano.

6
00:06:30.901 --> 00:06:33.320
Very good. A Cinzano.

7
00:06:33.862 --> 00:06:36.323
- And a vodka.
- Yes. sir.

8
00:06:43.956 --> 00:06:46.124
- You're not bored?
- Not at all.

9
00:06:46.208 --> 00:06:49.252
The Parisian in crowd
can be fascinating.

10
00:06:51.338 --> 00:06:53.256
What a scent.

11
00:06:53.340 --> 00:06:55.592
Scents are like memories.

12
00:06:55.676 --> 00:07:00.013
The person evaporates.
but the memory remains.

13
00:07:26.540 --> 00:07:28.041
<i>Mommy.</i>

14
00:07:30.127 --> 00:07:32.254
<i>Mommy. Daddy.</i>

15
00:07:34.881 --> 00:07:36.758
<i>I'm lost.</i>

16
00:07:38.760 --> 00:07:41.054
<i>I'm scared.</i>

17
00:08:44.284 --> 00:08:46.286
Why are you crying?

18
00:08:46.912 --> 00:08:48.413
I'm not crying.

19
00:08:49.039 --> 00:08:50.540
Come in.

20
00:08:51.875 --> 00:08:53.960
I'm a bit scared.

21
00:08:54.753 --> 00:08:57.422
Open the gate and come in.

22
00:09:03.428 --> 00:09:05.597
You're all in white.

23
00:09:05.680 --> 00:09:10.644
I got lost following the big black dog
with the ripped ear.

24
00:09:11.186 --> 00:09:13.146
Are you still scared?

25
00:09:13.230 --> 00:09:15.440
- Do you live here?
- Yes.

26
00:09:38.463 --> 00:09:40.757
- You can sleep here.
- Are you staying with me?

27
00:09:40.841 --> 00:09:42.759
Yes. I'm staying with you.

28
00:09:44.803 --> 00:09:47.305
- What's wrong?
- I cut myself. Go to sleep.

29
00:09:47.389 --> 00:09:50.058
- I'll say my prayers.
- Never mind that.

30
00:09:50.142 --> 00:09:51.601
There are crucifixes.

31
00:09:51.685 --> 00:09:55.814
They're all dead. Don't worry.
Close your eyes.

32
00:09:55.897 --> 00:09:58.066
- Without praying?
- Yes.

33
00:10:00.068 --> 00:10:02.696
You're so beautiful all in white.

34
00:11:04.841 --> 00:11:06.801
You've got to wake up.

35
00:11:07.385 --> 00:11:09.095
But it's not light yet.

36
00:11:09.179 --> 00:11:11.765
Your mother is worried.
Hurry up.

37
00:11:12.307 --> 00:11:14.351
Will you give me a kiss?

38
00:11:31.493 --> 00:11:33.036
Leave quickly.

39
00:11:33.703 --> 00:11:36.873
Don't. Come back.
Come back and open the gate.

40
00:11:38.083 --> 00:11:40.418
I'll be back. I love you.

41
00:12:08.989 --> 00:12:10.949
Do you like it that much?

42
00:12:11.574 --> 00:12:13.702
I don't know.

43
00:12:18.206 --> 00:12:20.292
I'm looking for something.

44
00:12:21.293 --> 00:12:25.797
That landscape.
the one behind the bottle.

45
00:12:29.009 --> 00:12:30.218
Frederic.

46
00:12:31.052 --> 00:12:32.971
My glass is empty.

47
00:12:33.054 --> 00:12:36.683
Forgive me. Mother.
I'm not a very dutiful son.

48
00:12:46.526 --> 00:12:49.154
A port. for a change.

49
00:13:00.623 --> 00:13:03.918
- Frederic. I'm waiting.
- Sorry.

50
00:13:05.045 --> 00:13:07.714
- But that poster-
- What do you think of it?

51
00:13:08.673 --> 00:13:12.260
- It's very beautiful.
- Isn't it? You can feel it.

52
00:13:13.720 --> 00:13:15.805
That landscape.

53
00:13:19.267 --> 00:13:23.271
Those ruins you see there.
where are they?

54
00:13:25.273 --> 00:13:29.027
It's a nice place.
One of my photographers discovered it.

55
00:13:35.950 --> 00:13:38.119
My glass is empty too.

56
00:13:39.204 --> 00:13:43.249
But those ruins. that landscape.

57
00:13:44.417 --> 00:13:46.586
They're like a part of my childhood.

58
00:13:47.420 --> 00:13:50.006
I feel like I've been there before.

59
00:13:52.175 --> 00:13:54.928
Leave me alone.
I'm trying to remember.

60
00:13:55.011 --> 00:13:58.515
Oh. that's nice.
abandoning me for some old ruins.

61
00:14:01.559 --> 00:14:03.520
This is good.

62
00:14:04.104 --> 00:14:07.607
- The guy who gave you those photos...
- Which photos?

63
00:14:08.191 --> 00:14:11.319
The ruins on that poster.
Is he here?

64
00:14:11.403 --> 00:14:14.197
Actually. it's a woman.
and she just left.

65
00:14:14.823 --> 00:14:17.617
- Could I have her address?
- Of course.

66
00:14:17.700 --> 00:14:21.996
- Is that really necessary. Frederic?
- It's important to me.

67
00:14:22.664 --> 00:14:25.959
Come with me.
Please. excuse us.

68
00:14:35.301 --> 00:14:37.137
Tell me. Mother.

69
00:14:37.679 --> 00:14:38.888
Yes?

70
00:14:38.972 --> 00:14:42.809
What do you think
about the perfume poster?

71
00:14:43.309 --> 00:14:44.894
Not bad.

72
00:14:45.353 --> 00:14:47.439
Your jacket is all dirty.

73
00:14:51.276 --> 00:14:53.153
That landscape.

74
00:14:53.903 --> 00:14:57.657
You know. the one used
as a background on that poster.

75
00:14:59.367 --> 00:15:01.453
Does it remind you of anything?

76
00:15:01.536 --> 00:15:04.122
Why? Should it?

77
00:15:07.333 --> 00:15:10.837
I feel like I know it.

78
00:15:11.421 --> 00:15:13.131
It happens.

79
00:15:13.214 --> 00:15:16.217
Many landscapes
give you a feeling of déja vu.

80
00:15:17.093 --> 00:15:19.304
You don't look well.

81
00:15:20.805 --> 00:15:23.349
Looking at those ruins...

82
00:15:24.976 --> 00:15:26.978
...brings back...

83
00:15:29.481 --> 00:15:32.817
...memories... and images...

84
00:15:33.651 --> 00:15:35.820
...from when I was a child.

85
00:15:37.947 --> 00:15:40.825
There was a bridge. I think.

86
00:15:45.747 --> 00:15:48.041
You really don't remember anything?

87
00:15:50.877 --> 00:15:54.047
No. really.
I don't know that place.

88
00:15:55.924 --> 00:15:57.967
The evening has been a success.

89
00:15:58.051 --> 00:16:00.386
You're not listening to me.

90
00:16:03.014 --> 00:16:06.392
I'm talking about something
that's very important to me.

91
00:16:08.394 --> 00:16:10.730
You know that since Father's death

92
00:16:11.314 --> 00:16:14.192
I can't recall a part of my childhood.

93
00:16:14.901 --> 00:16:16.694
I have forgotten it.

94
00:16:20.281 --> 00:16:22.242
And that poster...

95
00:16:22.992 --> 00:16:26.079
...brings some images back to mind.

96
00:16:28.248 --> 00:16:29.791
Of somebody.

97
00:16:32.752 --> 00:16:34.462
A young girl.

98
00:16:38.758 --> 00:16:42.762
I have told you about your past
a hundred times.

99
00:16:43.429 --> 00:16:45.348
There was never any young girl.

100
00:16:47.642 --> 00:16:52.730
Be a good boy and come back
to the living room. I'm a bit cold.

101
00:16:52.814 --> 00:16:55.525
Shall I tell you the rest
or shall I shut up?

102
00:16:56.025 --> 00:16:57.777
Please. go on.

103
00:16:58.278 --> 00:16:59.862
It's amusing.

104
00:17:04.242 --> 00:17:08.037
I can see myself... as a little boy...

105
00:17:09.539 --> 00:17:13.876
...in those ruins with a young girl.

106
00:17:13.960 --> 00:17:15.628
She was very pretty.

107
00:17:16.170 --> 00:17:18.256
Dressed all in white.

108
00:17:18.881 --> 00:17:21.926
I slept next to her all night.

109
00:17:24.887 --> 00:17:29.058
We fell in love.
the way 12-year-olds do.

110
00:17:30.810 --> 00:17:32.478
You're not listening to me.

111
00:17:33.813 --> 00:17:38.735
Believe me. I'd remember
if you'd had an experience like that.

112
00:17:40.695 --> 00:17:43.531
I'm going to go and see those ruins.

113
00:17:44.824 --> 00:17:47.160
Do you know where they are?

114
00:17:47.243 --> 00:17:48.745
Not yet.

115
00:17:49.871 --> 00:17:52.165
The photographer will tell me.

116
00:17:52.832 --> 00:17:54.626
Who knows?

117
00:17:55.668 --> 00:17:58.004
The young girl might still be there.

118
00:17:58.087 --> 00:18:00.381
The one you dreamt of?

119
00:18:01.174 --> 00:18:05.553
I don't think it was just a dream.

120
00:18:14.187 --> 00:18:17.023
- Be careful. my child.
- Of what. Mother?

121
00:18:17.523 --> 00:18:19.359
I don't know.

122
00:18:20.026 --> 00:18:21.611
Of the night.

123
00:18:59.482 --> 00:19:01.234
More to the right.

124
00:19:54.829 --> 00:19:56.372
- Hello.
- Hello.

125
00:19:56.456 --> 00:20:01.043
- Can I have a word?
- Sure. Come in.

126
00:20:01.127 --> 00:20:04.797
I think we've already met.
haven't we?

127
00:20:06.466 --> 00:20:08.926
Ah. yes. I remember.

128
00:20:09.010 --> 00:20:12.054
- At the cocktail party.
- That's right.

129
00:20:12.138 --> 00:20:14.599
I'll be with you in a second.

130
00:20:14.682 --> 00:20:16.392
Hello.

131
00:20:23.316 --> 00:20:24.984
Is he my new partner?

132
00:20:25.359 --> 00:20:29.030
No. that's it for today.
You're free to go.

133
00:20:43.669 --> 00:20:46.088
- Have a seat.
- Thanks.

134
00:20:51.427 --> 00:20:53.679
What can I do for you?

135
00:20:53.763 --> 00:20:55.348
Well...

136
00:20:56.307 --> 00:20:59.227
...you sold a photograph...

137
00:20:59.310 --> 00:21:02.188
...of some ruins for a poster.

138
00:21:02.772 --> 00:21:04.607
For a poster?

139
00:21:04.690 --> 00:21:06.192
Yes. I remember.

140
00:21:06.275 --> 00:21:08.319
Have you got a copy?

141
00:21:08.402 --> 00:21:10.863
Yes. I think so. Wait a minute.

142
00:21:20.498 --> 00:21:21.999
This one?

143
00:21:25.545 --> 00:21:28.840
Yes. that's the one.

144
00:21:31.259 --> 00:21:33.386
What's the place called?

145
00:21:33.928 --> 00:21:35.721
Where is it?

146
00:21:35.805 --> 00:21:38.057
I can't tell you anything about it.

147
00:21:38.724 --> 00:21:40.017
Why?

148
00:21:40.101 --> 00:21:44.355
I was paid a lot of money
to forget all about it.

149
00:21:45.690 --> 00:21:50.570
It's just that I remember that place
from my childhood.

150
00:21:51.445 --> 00:21:53.573
I'd like to see it again.
that's all.

151
00:21:54.198 --> 00:21:58.035
There's no reason to hide it from me.

152
00:21:58.578 --> 00:22:02.039
I'm sorry.
I was paid to keep it quiet.

153
00:22:02.123 --> 00:22:05.126
Perhaps to keep it a secret from you.

154
00:22:06.711 --> 00:22:10.006
But that's ridiculous.
Who paid you?

155
00:22:12.216 --> 00:22:16.929
Oh. yes. of course.
You can't say anything.

156
00:22:18.890 --> 00:22:23.352
Wait a minute. I've got an appointment.
I need to get changed.

157
00:22:57.637 --> 00:22:59.680
Where did I put my dress?

158
00:23:01.057 --> 00:23:03.893
I like you. Come closer.

159
00:23:11.567 --> 00:23:13.945
Come to the aquarium tonight.

160
00:23:14.028 --> 00:23:18.074
I'll look in my files
and tell you where those ruins are.

161
00:23:18.157 --> 00:23:20.993
But the aquarium is closed at night.

162
00:23:21.077 --> 00:23:25.373
Not for a press photographer.
I'm doing a shoot there.

163
00:23:25.456 --> 00:23:28.000
Come at midnight.

164
00:25:07.892 --> 00:25:09.185
Miss?

165
00:25:10.269 --> 00:25:13.105
- Could you lend me your flashlight?
- Have you lost something?

166
00:25:30.790 --> 00:25:32.291
Thank you.

167
00:32:52.898 --> 00:32:54.775
Hello. Frederic.

168
00:32:58.070 --> 00:33:00.280
How do you know my name?

169
00:33:00.364 --> 00:33:03.742
I was the young girl.
Don't you remember?

170
00:33:04.409 --> 00:33:07.412
You were about 12 years old.

171
00:33:12.960 --> 00:33:16.630
In the countryside. near the ruins.

172
00:33:16.713 --> 00:33:18.298
You don't look like her.

173
00:33:18.924 --> 00:33:20.926
Does that matter?

174
00:33:24.179 --> 00:33:26.098
I don't know.

175
00:33:28.350 --> 00:33:30.936
Why are you here tonight?

176
00:33:32.187 --> 00:33:34.606
More than 20 years have gone by.

177
00:33:35.148 --> 00:33:36.608
That's true.

178
00:33:37.609 --> 00:33:41.321
Earlier. I thought I saw you
as you were 20 years ago.

179
00:33:42.281 --> 00:33:46.493
Come. This night will be ours.

180
00:40:17.842 --> 00:40:19.260
Tell me.

181
00:40:20.887 --> 00:40:22.681
Twenty years ago.

182
00:40:23.223 --> 00:40:26.476
...a little boy gave you his toy.

183
00:40:28.561 --> 00:40:30.522
What was that toy?

184
00:40:36.319 --> 00:40:39.114
I didn't believe your story
for a second.

185
00:40:40.365 --> 00:40:42.659
I don't know
who you're all working for...

186
00:40:43.201 --> 00:40:45.286
...or why you don't want me
to find the girl.

187
00:40:45.370 --> 00:40:49.874
But you can tell your employer
that I'm not about to give up.

188
00:49:30.228 --> 00:49:31.062
POWER

189
00:50:49.974 --> 00:50:52.727
- They tried to kill me.
- What?

190
00:50:55.062 --> 00:50:57.023
You're soaked.

191
00:50:57.607 --> 00:50:59.400
They want my head.

192
00:50:59.483 --> 00:51:01.652
Get changed. You're freezing.

193
00:51:05.406 --> 00:51:07.617
I saw her dead.

194
00:51:08.826 --> 00:51:10.077
Murdered.

195
00:51:10.161 --> 00:51:11.621
Who?

196
00:51:11.704 --> 00:51:13.497
The photographer!

197
00:51:13.998 --> 00:51:16.167
She was waiting for me.

198
00:51:16.709 --> 00:51:18.669
So they decided to kill her.

199
00:51:20.338 --> 00:51:21.922
It's crazy.

200
00:51:22.506 --> 00:51:26.010
Just because she wanted to tell me
the name of those ruins.

201
00:51:28.262 --> 00:51:30.514
I was alone with her dead body.

202
00:51:32.933 --> 00:51:36.771
- I ran away.
- Good. You could have been accused.

203
00:51:37.563 --> 00:51:39.190
A bat.

204
00:51:39.857 --> 00:51:41.525
A huge bat.

205
00:51:41.609 --> 00:51:43.444
A monster in the coffin.

206
00:51:45.071 --> 00:51:46.572
What are you saying?

207
00:51:47.782 --> 00:51:49.492
She's real.

208
00:51:50.368 --> 00:51:52.036
I saw her.

209
00:51:52.870 --> 00:51:54.455
Or...

210
00:51:55.539 --> 00:51:57.124
Or otherwise I'm mad.

211
00:51:57.208 --> 00:52:00.878
Relax. Get changed
and then I'll listen to you.

212
00:52:20.106 --> 00:52:21.607
He's come back.

213
00:52:21.691 --> 00:52:23.943
He's acting like a madman.
Come straightaway.

214
00:52:33.661 --> 00:52:35.538
She was there.

215
00:52:36.372 --> 00:52:38.082
Her white figure.

216
00:52:40.418 --> 00:52:42.086
The same girl.

217
00:52:43.838 --> 00:52:45.506
She hadn't changed.

218
00:52:46.090 --> 00:52:49.552
I don't understand.
You're not making sense.

219
00:52:51.262 --> 00:52:55.891
They desperately tried to stop me
from finding the girl and the place.

220
00:52:55.975 --> 00:52:58.602
But who and what
are you talking about?

221
00:52:59.103 --> 00:53:00.730
The ruins.

222
00:53:01.272 --> 00:53:03.274
The ruins in the photograph.

223
00:53:03.858 --> 00:53:07.653
They are linked to my childhood.
I want to find them.

224
00:53:09.697 --> 00:53:11.699
That's why they killed her.

225
00:53:14.201 --> 00:53:15.953
Who? Where?

226
00:53:17.329 --> 00:53:20.458
All my life. with all my strength.

227
00:53:20.541 --> 00:53:26.088
I've tried to give you the childhood
you lost after your father's death.

228
00:53:26.589 --> 00:53:30.426
The two of us have patiently rebuilt...

229
00:53:30.509 --> 00:53:35.097
Unfortunately.
I've always felt a stranger

230
00:53:35.181 --> 00:53:37.767
to the childhood you describe.

231
00:53:38.809 --> 00:53:42.188
That has been the root
of all your anguish. and your visions.

232
00:53:42.271 --> 00:53:44.774
Like this young girl. for example.

233
00:53:45.316 --> 00:53:48.694
I saw her tonight.

234
00:53:49.320 --> 00:53:51.947
She was calling me and enticing me.

235
00:53:52.698 --> 00:53:54.658
...as if she needed my help.

236
00:53:55.159 --> 00:53:58.746
It's you who needs help.
from a good doctor.

237
00:54:00.831 --> 00:54:03.334
You want me to believe that I'm mad.

238
00:54:03.417 --> 00:54:06.504
I just want you to go and see my doctor.

239
00:54:06.587 --> 00:54:07.880
Enough.

240
00:54:09.215 --> 00:54:11.801
That's enough.
or I'll smash this place up!

241
00:54:18.057 --> 00:54:21.811
Until I've found that young girl
and those ruins.

242
00:54:21.894 --> 00:54:24.563
...I won't set foot
in this house again.

243
00:55:33.841 --> 00:55:35.801
You're looking at me...

244
00:55:37.261 --> 00:55:41.432
...as if you can actually see me.

245
00:55:48.981 --> 00:55:53.819
If you don't really exist.

246
00:55:56.113 --> 00:55:58.407
...then I know that I'm mad.

247
00:55:59.283 --> 00:56:00.951
Really mad.

248
00:56:05.289 --> 00:56:08.334
I feel completely imprisoned.

249
00:56:09.585 --> 00:56:11.086
My head.

250
00:56:11.629 --> 00:56:13.130
My memory.

251
00:56:16.508 --> 00:56:18.469
You. standing there in front of me.

252
00:56:20.054 --> 00:56:22.264
Even when I close my eyes.

253
00:56:23.807 --> 00:56:27.645
I beg you. if you do exist.

254
00:56:27.728 --> 00:56:32.149
...if you're alive somewhere.
if I can find you again.

255
00:56:32.232 --> 00:56:37.071
...if you're not just a vision
from my childhood dreams.

256
00:56:37.154 --> 00:56:38.739
...then talk to me.

257
00:56:38.822 --> 00:56:40.824
Tell me that you can hear me.

258
00:56:41.450 --> 00:56:43.994
I'll find the place
where you're imprisoned.

259
00:56:48.707 --> 00:56:50.834
I love you.

260
00:57:28.038 --> 00:57:29.790
Have you calmed down?

261
00:57:29.873 --> 00:57:31.625
Good.

262
00:57:31.709 --> 00:57:36.213
We're going to administer
a short series of electric shocks.

263
00:57:36.296 --> 00:57:38.924
- Don't be afraid. but...
- You bastard.

264
00:57:41.093 --> 00:57:43.137
Who paid you?

265
00:57:43.220 --> 00:57:44.722
Bastard!

266
00:57:46.473 --> 00:57:49.810
Don't be angry.
I use good old-fashioned methods.

267
00:57:49.893 --> 00:57:51.895
They've been tried and tested.

268
00:57:53.272 --> 00:57:56.942
You're in safe hands.
In very safe hands.

269
00:59:48.178 --> 00:59:50.639
Sauveterre Castle.

270
00:59:58.939 --> 01:00:00.524
<i>Platform 9.</i>

271
01:00:00.607 --> 01:00:02.734
<i>Watch the doors.</i>

272
01:00:02.818 --> 01:00:07.698
<i>The train is about to leave.</i>

273
01:06:31.540 --> 01:06:35.877
Frederic. I'm here to stop you
from freeing the woman

274
01:06:35.961 --> 01:06:40.799
...who brought so much pain
to your father and me.

275
01:06:42.300 --> 01:06:46.429
You. and your father and I
lived nearby.

276
01:06:47.138 --> 01:06:50.308
You didn't know
that she was also living with us.

277
01:06:52.102 --> 01:06:53.895
She was locked up.

278
01:06:53.979 --> 01:06:55.689
...hidden away...

279
01:06:56.439 --> 01:07:00.110
...for eternity at the age of 16.

280
01:07:00.652 --> 01:07:04.406
At night. she would escape.

281
01:07:04.948 --> 01:07:08.535
One evening.
you met her in these ruins.

282
01:07:09.703 --> 01:07:11.454
I knew it.

283
01:07:12.414 --> 01:07:14.291
You lied to me.

284
01:07:14.833 --> 01:07:19.045
I knew that meeting really happened.
that she was real.

285
01:07:19.129 --> 01:07:22.799
Like vampires. like the living dead.

286
01:07:23.466 --> 01:07:26.511
Vampirism is a terrible affliction.

287
01:07:27.470 --> 01:07:30.348
The little girl infected several people.

288
01:07:30.432 --> 01:07:32.976
Our relatives. our friends.

289
01:07:34.185 --> 01:07:37.105
I had to reveal my secret
to the town mayor.

290
01:07:37.188 --> 01:07:39.774
...especially after the
death of your father.

291
01:07:40.650 --> 01:07:42.819
But it was already too late.

292
01:07:42.902 --> 01:07:46.448
Four other young girls
had become monsters too.

293
01:07:48.491 --> 01:07:51.161
<i>When night fell on the fields.</i>

294
01:07:51.745 --> 01:07:55.790
<i>...they would attack and kill anyone
who approached the ruins.</i>

295
01:07:56.541 --> 01:08:00.879
<i>Sometimes. we could hear
their victims' screams from afar.</i>

296
01:09:25.755 --> 01:09:28.967
<i>Little Jennifer
would take them into the castle...</i>

297
01:09:29.050 --> 01:09:31.136
<i>...and lead them
to their horrible fate.</i>

298
01:09:32.470 --> 01:09:35.098
<i>Then. one day.</i>

299
01:09:35.974 --> 01:09:40.186
<i>...I plucked up enough courage...</i>

300
01:09:40.270 --> 01:09:42.313
<i>...and I tried to kill her.</i>

301
01:09:42.439 --> 01:09:45.734
I drove a stake through her heart.

302
01:09:45.817 --> 01:09:49.154
But I had to sever her head
from her body.

303
01:09:49.237 --> 01:09:51.448
...and I wasn't brave enough to do that.

304
01:09:52.157 --> 01:09:55.952
So I entombed her in these ruins.

305
01:09:56.703 --> 01:09:58.246
Alive.

306
01:09:59.998 --> 01:10:03.209
Locked away for eternity.

307
01:10:07.964 --> 01:10:12.218
<i>We couldn't bring ourselves
to kill the four girls either.</i>

308
01:10:12.302 --> 01:10:16.264
<i>During the day. vampires must rest
where they are buried.</i>

309
01:10:16.347 --> 01:10:19.976
<i>We moved their bodies
into abandoned vaults in Paris.</i>

310
01:10:20.059 --> 01:10:23.605
<i>They were alive.
but they couldn't escape.</i>

311
01:10:23.688 --> 01:10:26.274
It was you who freed them.

312
01:10:26.357 --> 01:10:28.151
A vampire?

313
01:10:29.986 --> 01:10:32.238
So...

314
01:10:32.322 --> 01:10:34.574
...she is still alive?

315
01:10:34.657 --> 01:10:39.078
We're going to destroy them
before this curse spreads.

316
01:13:33.211 --> 01:13:36.965
At dawn. a short while ago.

317
01:13:37.840 --> 01:13:40.635
...they came back
to reclaim their home.

318
01:13:41.803 --> 01:13:44.764
We were brave enough to destroy them.

319
01:13:45.682 --> 01:13:50.520
Have the courage
to kill the monster in this dungeon...

320
01:13:50.603 --> 01:13:52.939
...who you nearly brought back to life.

321
01:13:53.022 --> 01:13:56.401
The female vampires
will stay out in daylight.

322
01:13:56.484 --> 01:13:58.569
We'll burn them tonight.

323
01:13:58.653 --> 01:14:02.949
When night falls.
bring us Jennifer's head.

324
01:14:13.960 --> 01:14:15.503
Go.

325
01:14:17.547 --> 01:14:19.549
She killed your father.

326
01:16:01.150 --> 01:16:03.152
Light the fire.

327
01:16:21.546 --> 01:16:23.923
Throw on the bodies.

328
01:17:41.542 --> 01:17:42.752
Come.

329
01:17:44.253 --> 01:17:45.922
Let's leave.

330
01:17:48.382 --> 01:17:50.301
We must forget everything.

331
01:17:51.510 --> 01:17:53.221
Later.

332
01:17:53.304 --> 01:17:54.805
You go.

333
01:17:57.725 --> 01:17:59.852
I want to stay here alone.

334
01:18:47.900 --> 01:18:51.612
You're the little boy
who gave me his toy.

335
01:19:01.956 --> 01:19:05.001
I've watched you for many years
without being able to speak to you.

336
01:19:05.084 --> 01:19:09.088
You had to remember me
before I could appear to you.

337
01:19:30.860 --> 01:19:35.448
The old woman put all my things here
so nothing was left of me outside.

338
01:19:35.531 --> 01:19:37.992
My whole life up until
the age of 16 is in here.

339
01:19:42.038 --> 01:19:45.833
I read and reread this book
when I was in my coffin.

340
01:19:48.502 --> 01:19:50.796
Before I could project my body
to the outside world.

341
01:19:50.880 --> 01:19:52.840
...I learnt to project my sight.

342
01:19:54.800 --> 01:19:57.553
I read this book
without leaving my coffin.

343
01:20:06.979 --> 01:20:09.857
I've never actually been
to this beach before.

344
01:20:11.233 --> 01:20:13.861
I've only seen it from my coffin.

345
01:20:14.612 --> 01:20:19.658
I've dreamt about running
along this beach. You see. it's ours.

346
01:20:21.243 --> 01:20:23.579
I've thought about it for 20 years.

347
01:20:23.662 --> 01:20:26.374
Look. I'm free!

348
01:20:27.750 --> 01:20:29.377
Music!

349
01:20:31.212 --> 01:20:36.092
Look at the brass instruments.
with a mad conductor leading them!

350
01:20:36.175 --> 01:20:38.135
They're going to break everything!

351
01:20:40.096 --> 01:20:41.931
Listen.

352
01:21:11.127 --> 01:21:13.462
I used to come here as a spirit too.

353
01:21:14.130 --> 01:21:19.260
Without realizing it. by closing the gate
the little boy shut me in.

354
01:21:41.490 --> 01:21:44.702
I saw my abandoned toy
rusting away all alone.

355
01:21:44.785 --> 01:21:48.706
I thought it would be the first thing
I'd look for when I was free.

356
01:23:05.157 --> 01:23:08.953
The tide will carry us
out into the ocean.

357
01:23:09.620 --> 01:23:11.580
...to a desert island.

358
01:23:12.540 --> 01:23:14.458
They won't find us.

359
01:23:15.793 --> 01:23:19.547
It's called Sand Island.

360
01:23:20.589 --> 01:23:22.007
Come.

361
01:23:27.846 --> 01:23:31.642
There we'll lure rich sailors.

362
01:23:31.725 --> 01:23:35.437
- You're like me now.
- I'm just starting to live.

362
01:23:36.305 --> 01:24:36.832
